span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> they would have to be ordered to create one only , as was suggested. Two registers confuses the trade ,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> while the general public have not the slightest idea what </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">its</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> all about . </span></li><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; orphans:0; padding-left:6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The positive side of Part P is a general change of attitude amongst registered, self employed</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> electricians, new and old , towards safety , sticking to the regulations</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and working in a responsible manner .</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> Knowledge and skills levels are much higher than ,say, ten years ago. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> This is mainly due to the yearly inspection and the registering of domestic work with Local Building Control.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; orphans:0; padding-left:6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The negative side however , which was not touched upon in the HOC Committee Meeting is the new , worrying</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> phenomenon of pushing would- be electricians of all ages , through short college courses , most of them completing the courses without any practical onsite site experience whatsoever. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> I'm afraid they are referred to in the trade as " 5 Week Wonders". I believe the modern apprenticeship is 4 years , based on City &amp; Guilds and practical hands on , site work with trained electricians.  The older apprenticeships were 6 years .  A 5 week course and a bit of paper does not make you an electrician , </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">its</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> frightening to say the least. Sometimes these courses are called</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> "Part P " courses , which actually means nothing in that context . Competent Persons schemes will of course , sign them up to increase membership , I would imagine.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; orphans:0; padding-left:6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">If Part P is to continue then the number of operating</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> schemes needs to be reduced , far too many ,and totally confusing to the customer</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> who may have heard of possibly one scheme ,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> so the register is the important thing to promote , as with Gas Safe . </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> The schemes are fighting to dominate the industry and it does no one any good whatsoever .  As an afterthought , the real backbone of the industry , the electrician with his van and his toolbox is hardly considered , other than paying his yearly dues to fund it all. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">In ending , I must say that I was impressed with the professional attitude of the HOC Committee. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>